The paper discusses online learning algorithms for supervised learning problems, which are typically studied in the machine learning community. The focus is on pairwise loss functions, which are commonly used in metric learning and ranking problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses memory-efficient algorithms and convergence rates, which are topics that fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory), respectively.
